Questions:
Which of the following is considered the experimental component of the Fish and Fiber study?
A) Routine blood tests conducted by your primary care physician;
B) Daily consumption of fish oil and fiber supplements or placebo for 30 days each period;
C) Standard clinical care for any unrelated medical conditions;
D) Collection of personal health and dietary habit information at the beginning of the study.

Correct answer: B) Daily consumption of fish oil and fiber supplements or placebo for 30 days each period.

If you experience an adverse event or have a medical emergency related to the study, whom should you contact immediately?

A) The Institutional Review Office Director at Fred Hutchinson Cancer Research Center;
B) The Principal Investigator, Dr. Johanna Lampe, or the Project Manager, Lisa Levy;
C) Your personal physician;
D) The US Food and Drug Administration (FDA).

Correct answer: B) The Principal Investigator, Dr. Johanna Lampe, or the Project Manager, Lisa Levy.
